commentTextItems.html: That's that! Nepal win by six wickets and 42 balls to spare. A proper thumping. Airee it is who gets the winning runs. Right in the slot on middle stump. He waits for it and smashes it straight down the ground. All smiles in the Nepal camp and they get on the board with two points.

commentPostTextItems.html: Nepal collect two points while USA have a lot of thinking to do. In case you missed the action, PDP has you covered with his report. That will be it from us today but we will be back tomorrow nice and early for the two games. Till then, this is Ashish Pant, signing off on behalf of Peter Della Penna and K Vairavan. Ciao!
Kalpit Dhakal: "Dipendra Singh Airee back in form, major positive of this match."

Rohit Paudel, Nepal captain: Happy with the performance of teh team. We were looking for a win and we got it. He [Karan KC] was brilliant. He used the conditions really well. He and Lalit bowled very well and that set the tone for us. His [Rajbanshi's] contribution is main, and that helped Karan. [Batting] Bhim batted really well, and Deepi da also batted well. We hope to not make the same mistakes again. [West Indies match] We all are looking forward to the match. We want everyone to contribute in that game, and we have to play our best cricket.

Aaron Jones, USA captain: [The target] It was enough, but we did not bowl well. The wicket started playing better in the second innings. It was a bit tough at the top but Shayan played a good innings. Very happy for him. We have lost the first two games, but we are positive we can win and qualify for the World Cup.

Karan KC is the Player of the Match: It was just the plan. If we won the toss, we had to bowl and I got the basics right. I really enjoyed the opening spell. The ball was doing enough, and it was my ideal length. Very important win, we have two games and we have to win at least one of the games and qualify for the top six. The batters played really well. Sharki enjoyed his batting, and we were also enjoying from the outside.

4.21pm A performance right out of the top drawer from Nepal. It was Karan KC who set the tone with the ball a four-wicket haul up top and Ben Sharki setup the chase, scoring an unbeaten 114-ball 77. That USA got to 207 was all down to Shayan Jahangir's maiden ODI century. However, the target was always expected to be within Nepal's grasp. They need a good start, which was provided by Kushal Burtel and Sharki who added 49 runs for the second wicket. Paudel and Sharki then pitched in important contributions before USA got back with a couple of wickets. However, Dipendra Singh Airee was quick off the blocks and that rubbed on Sharki, who begann playing his shots. The duo added 74 runs off 64 and took Nepal to an easy win in the end.

seriesStandings.notes:
In the event of teams finishing on equal points in their Group
a) The team with the greatest number of wins in its Group will be placed in the higher position.
b) If there are teams with equal points and equal wins in the Group stage, then in such case the team with the higher net run rate in the Group stage will be placed in the higher position
c) If two or more teams are still equal, they will be ordered according to the head to head match played between them (points then net run rate in those matches).
d) If the above does not resolve the Group ordering, or if all matches within a Group produce no results, then any tied teams will be ordered as per their original Group Stage seedings and the top 3 teams in each Group will progress to the Super Six stage.
In the event of teams finishing on equal points in the Super Six stage a) The team with the greatest number of wins in all of the matches throughout the competition against the other Super Six stage qualifiers will be placed in the higher position.
b) If there are teams with equal points and equal wins in the Super Six stage, then in such case the team with the higher net run rate in all matches played against the other Super Six qualifiers will be placed in the higher position
c) If two or more teams are still equal, they will be ordered according to the head-to-head match(es) played between them (points then net run rate in those matches).
d) If still equal, any teams that cannot be separated in this way shall be placed according to their original Group seeding.
e) If the above does not resolve the Super Six stage ordering, or if all matches within the Super Six stage produce no results, then the order of finishing will be determined by the team's performances in the Group stage as follows: Group standing, most points, most wins. If still equal, any teams that cannot be separated in this way shall be placed according to their original Group ranking.
